SECURITY.md
# Security Policy

## Overview
Gifted Hands Innovation is committed to maintaining the security and integrity of our website and ensuring a safe browsing experience for all users. Our site displays car accessory recommendations and may include affiliate links to third-party retailers such as Amazon. We do not collect sensitive user information, but we still take website security seriously.

---

## Supported Versions
Because this is a static website hosted on GitHub Pages, only the latest live version is supported.

| Version     | Supported |
|-------------|-----------|
| Latest      | Yes       |
| Older builds| No        |

---

## Reporting a Vulnerability
If you discover any vulnerability, broken link behavior, or suspicious activity related to our website, please report it responsibly.

### Please include:
- A clear description of the issue  
- Steps to reproduce it  
- Any screenshots or sample code  
- What you believe the risk may be  

### Report to:
**Email:** giftedhandsinnovation@gmail.com  
(If you donâ€™t have this email yet, we can create a Gmail for your brand.)

We will make every effort to acknowledge your report within **72 hours** and resolve confirmed issues as quickly as possible.

---

## Scope of Security Testing
### In-Scope
- HTML, CSS, JavaScript used on this website  
- GitHub Pages hosting configuration  
- Broken redirects or unsafe external links  
- Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities  
- Incorrect or unsafe use of Amazon affiliate links  

### Out-of-Scope
- Issues on Amazon or any third-party websites  
- Browser-side extensions or modifications  
- Network issues unrelated to our website  
- Denial-of-service testing or spam attacks  

---

## Responsible Disclosure
We ask that all security findings be reported **privately first**, and not publicly disclosed until they are reviewed and resolved.  
We appreciate all efforts to improve the safety and reliability of our website.

Thank you for helping us maintain a secure platform.
